<node CREATED="1372791437850" ID="ID_992026119" MODIFIED="1372863335206" TEXT="New Mindmap">
<node COLOR="#cc6600" CREATED="1372791448803" ID="ID_1549936806" MODIFIED="1372792169472" POSITION="right" TEXT="Intro -- explanation ">
<node CREATED="1372755989027" ID="ID_789261400" MODIFIED="1372757639688" TEXT="Previous sections were mainly looking at what social skills curricula focus on and where the challenges lie (sec 2-4). We then provided examples to show how these challenges and learning principles are likely to be supported by technology, and drew out some of the research that is already very relevant to these domains (sec 5) -- however, this was still structured by the learning principles and social skills learning challenges (showing that HCI has value to add)."/>
<node CREATED="1372757526705" ID="ID_1190749306" MODIFIED="1372757921347" TEXT=" This section attempts to counterbalance this by taking a HCI stance again, briefly discussing the challenges and opportunities research in this domain would pose for *HCI* "/>
</node>
<node COLOR="#cc6600" CREATED="1372792109505" ID="ID_194901329" MODIFIED="1372863335322" POSITION="right" TEXT="Two and half settings - inside, outside (and connecting these)">
